      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "349eeb84933c0e73",
      "text": "Only now educators are taken out of the business of dressage, of the sheer imparting of knowledge for the purposes of a corporative way of life and no longer have to reserve only special attention for (risky) deviations that occur here and there, but fundamentally and always take into account the individuality of the individuals, and just for this it is simply indispensable to have at least one anchor point, the ONE of the person, the minimal [[Unity]] of the social address of their clientele.\n"
