      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "11de52c2429624fd",
      "text": "Thus education becomes a tightrope walk between the triviality of pure knowledge transfer and the emerging non-triviality of the social address. On the one hand, the task is to keep trivial machines in operation, on the other hand (and increasingly) to de-trivialize trivial machines, i.e. to fit them into the new [[Address Form of Education]] - a task that, as is easy to understand, can only overtax and eventually drives many who do education professionally into burn-out."
