    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "d7bd9b1f21ada60a",
      "text": "The situation becomes disastrous (or less pathetically: extremely complex) when the laborious adjustment of education to the new address format is confronted with the fact that under modern (world) social conditions the address no longer conforms to the image that education has of it in central respects. In other words: The ONE-ness of the address is blown up. It becomes polycontextual, heterarchic, hypercomplex, it takes the form of an inconclusive list. And - horribile dictu -: Education as a functional system of society is directly involved in this process."
